  "page": "Rhaenyra the Cruel",
  "html": "<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><table class=\"infobox\" style=\"min-width:22em;max-width:32em;border-collapse:separate;border-spacing:3px\"><tbody><tr><th colspan=\"2\" style=\"text-align:center;font-size:125%;font-weight:bold;background-color:rgb(248, 233, 208);border:none;\">\"Rhaenyra the Cruel\"</th></tr><tr><td colspan=\"2\" style=\"text-align:center;font-size: 100%\">\n<i><a href=\"/index.php/House_of_the_Dragon\" title=\"House of the Dragon\">House of the Dragon</a></i></td></tr><tr><td colspan=\"2\" style=\"text-align:center\">\n<table style=\"width:100%;\">\n<tbody><tr style=\"vertical-align:top;\">\n<td style=\"width:50%;text-align:right;\">Season 2</td>\n<td style=\"text-align:center;\">&#160;—&#160;</td>\n<td style=\"width:50%;text-align:left;\">Episode 2</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody></table></td></tr><tr><td colspan=\"2\" class=\"infobox-image\" style=\"text-align:center\">\n<a href=\"/index.php/File:Rhaenyra_the_Cruel_HOTD.jpeg\" class=\"image\"><img alt=\"Rhaenyra the Cruel HOTD.jpeg\" src=\"/images/thumb/c/ce/Rhaenyra_the_Cruel_HOTD.jpeg/300px-Rhaenyra_the_Cruel_HOTD.jpeg\" width=\"300\" height=\"169\" class=\"thumbborder\" srcset=\"/images/thumb/c/ce/Rhaenyra_the_Cruel_HOTD.jpeg/450px-Rhaenyra_the_Cruel_HOTD.jpeg 1.5x, /images/thumb/c/ce/Rhaenyra_the_Cruel_HOTD.jpeg/600px-Rhaenyra_the_Cruel_HOTD.jpeg 2x\" /></a></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Original air date</th><td>\nJune 23, 2024</td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Running time</th><td>\n69 minutes</td></tr><tr><th colspan=\"2\" style=\"text-align:center;background-color:#f8e9d0;border:none;\">Credits</th></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Directed by</th><td class=\"plainlist\">\n<a href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Clare_Kilner\" class=\"extiw\" title=\"w:Clare Kilner\">Clare Kilner</a></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Written by</th><td class=\"plainlist\">\n<a href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Sara_Hess\" class=\"extiw\" title=\"w:Sara Hess\">Sara Hess</a></td></tr><tr><th colspan=\"2\" style=\"text-align:center;background-color:#f8e9d0;border:none;\">Episode chronology</th></tr><tr><td colspan=\"2\" style=\"text-align:center\">\n<table style=\"width:100%;\">\n<tbody><tr style=\"vertical-align:top;\">\n<th style=\"width:50%;text-align:center;\">←&#160;Previous</th>\n<th style=\"width:50%;text-align:center;\">Next&#160;→</th>\n</tr><tr style=\"vertical-align:top;\">\n<td style=\"text-align:center;\">\"<a href=\"/index.php/A_Son_for_a_Son_(TV)\" title=\"A Son for a Son (TV)\">A Son for a Son</a>\"</td>\n<td style=\"text-align:center;\">\"<a href=\"/index.php/The_Burning_Mill\" title=\"The Burning Mill\">The Burning Mill</a>\"</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody></table></td></tr><tr><td colspan=\"2\" style=\"text-align:center;background-color:#f8e9d0;border:none;\">\n<a href=\"/index.php/List_of_House_of_the_Dragon_episodes\" title=\"List of House of the Dragon episodes\">List of episodes</a></td></tr></tbody></table>\n<p>\"<b>Rhaenyra the Cruel</b>\" is the second episode of <a href=\"/index.php/House_of_the_Dragon_-_Season_2\" title=\"House of the Dragon - Season 2\">season two</a> of the HBO <a href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/medieval_fantasy\" class=\"extiw\" title=\"w:medieval fantasy\">medieval fantasy</a> television series <i><a href=\"/index.php/House_of_the_Dragon\" title=\"House of the Dragon\">House of the Dragon</a></i>. Running 69 minutes long, it premiered on June 23, 2024. The episode was written by writer and executive producer <a href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Sara_Hess\" class=\"extiw\" title=\"w:Sara Hess\">Sara Hess</a> and directed by returning director <a href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Clare_Kilner\" class=\"extiw\" title=\"w:Clare Kilner\">Clare Kilner</a>. Music was composed by <a href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Ramin_Djawadi\" class=\"extiw\" title=\"w:Ramin Djawadi\">Ramin Djawadi</a>.\n</p>\n<div id=\"toc\" class=\"toc\"><div class=\"toctitle\" lang=\"en\" dir=\"ltr\"><h2>Contents</h2></div>\n<ul>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-1\"><a href=\"#Official_synopsis\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">1</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Official synopsis</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-2\"><a href=\"#Plot\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">2</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Plot</span></a>\n<ul>\n<li class=\"toclevel-2 tocsection-3\"><a href=\"#King.27s_Landing\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">2.1</span> <span class=\"toctext\">King's Landing</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-2 tocsection-4\"><a href=\"#Driftmark\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">2.2</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Driftmark</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-2 tocsection-5\"><a href=\"#Dragonstone\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">2.3</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Dragonstone</span></a></li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-6\"><a href=\"#Cast\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">3</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Cast</span></a>\n<ul>\n<li class=\"toclevel-2 tocsection-7\"><a href=\"#Starring\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">3.1</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Starring</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-2 tocsection-8\"><a href=\"#Co-starring\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">3.2</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Co-starring</span></a></li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-9\"><a href=\"#Reception\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">4</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Reception</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-10\"><a href=\"#References\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">5</span> <span class=\"toctext\">References</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-11\"><a href=\"#External_links\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">6</span> <span class=\"toctext\">External links</span></a></li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Official_synopsis\">Official synopsis</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Rhaenyra_the_Cruel&amp;action=edit&amp;section=1\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: Official synopsis\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<p>As Otto schemes to turn the public against her, Rhaenyra questions Daemon’s loyalty. Meanwhile, Ser Criston Cole concocts a misguided plan for revenge.<sup id=\"cite_ref-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Plot\">Plot</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Rhaenyra_the_Cruel&amp;action=edit&amp;section=2\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: Plot\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<div role=\"note\" class=\"hatnote navigation-not-searchable\" style=\"font-style: italic;padding-left: 1.6em;margin-bottom: 0.5em;\">See also: <a href=\"/index.php/Differences_between_Fire_%26_Blood_and_House_of_the_Dragon\" title=\"Differences between Fire &amp; Blood and House of the Dragon\">Differences between Fire &amp; Blood and House of the Dragon</a></div>\n<h3><span id=\"King's_Landing\"></span><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"King.27s_Landing\">King's Landing</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Rhaenyra_the_Cruel&amp;action=edit&amp;section=3\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: King&#039;s Landing\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h3>\n<p>News of Prince <a href=\"/index.php/Jaehaerys_Targaryen_(son_of_Aegon_II)\" title=\"Jaehaerys Targaryen (son of Aegon II)\">Jaehaerys Targaryen</a> spreads in the <a href=\"/index.php/Red_Keep\" title=\"Red Keep\">Red Keep</a>; King <a href=\"/index.php/Aegon_II_Targaryen\" title=\"Aegon II Targaryen\">Aegon II Targaryen</a> is furious, the servants are assembled and questioned, the gates of the city have been shut and the search for the assassins has began. Returning to his chambers, Prince <a href=\"/index.php/Aemond_Targaryen\" title=\"Aemond Targaryen\">Aemond Targaryen</a> finds the <a href=\"/index.php/Currency\" title=\"Currency\">coins</a> he left on his table have been taken and a secret passageway is open in the wall, he deduces the assassins have been in his room and he may have been the intended target. <a href=\"/index.php/Alicent_Hightower\" title=\"Alicent Hightower\">Alicent Hightower</a> believes the death of her grandson is a retribution from the <a href=\"/index.php/The_Seven\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"The Seven\">gods</a> caused by her carnal sins with Ser <a href=\"/index.php/Criston_Cole\" title=\"Criston Cole\">Criston Cole</a>.\n</p><p>In the small council meeting, Ser <a href=\"/index.php/Otto_Hightower\" title=\"Otto Hightower\">Otto Hightower</a> intents on using Jaehaerys's death as a propaganda tool against <a href=\"/index.php/Rhaenyra_Targaryen\" title=\"Rhaenyra Targaryen\">Rhaenyra Targaryen</a>. He wishes to expose the child's body to the populace of <a href=\"/index.php/King%27s_Landing\" title=\"King&#39;s Landing\">King's Landing</a> in a funeral procession to earn the <a href=\"/index.php/Smallfolk\" title=\"Smallfolk\">smallfolk</a>'s sympaties and to pass the blame of his death on Rhaenyra. Aegon first rejects the idea but later accepts. Lord <a href=\"/index.php/Larys_Strong\" title=\"Larys Strong\">Larys Strong</a> enters the room with the news they have apprehended a <a href=\"/index.php/Gold_cloak\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Gold cloak\">Gold cloak</a> with the child's head in his possession at the <a href=\"/index.php/Gate_of_the_Gods\" title=\"Gate of the Gods\">Gate of the Gods</a>. <a href=\"/index.php/Blood_(butcher)\" title=\"Blood (butcher)\">Blood</a> confesses everything to Larys at the sight of his <a href=\"/index.php/Torture\" title=\"Torture\">torture</a> tools, but that does not save him as King Aegon beats him to death with a mace.\n</p><p>Alicent informs her daughter, Queen <a href=\"/index.php/Helaena_Targaryen\" title=\"Helaena Targaryen\">Helaena Targaryen</a>, they are both required to participate in the procession as representatives of the crown. Helena reluctantly accepts. During the procession, Helaena has a panic attack as the smallfolk cry her name and approach her.\n</p><p>As she prepares for her bath, Alicent asks Criston if he told anybody about their affair. The knight says no but he is blaming himself for not being there to protect Helaena and her children. Criston confronts his fellow <a href=\"/index.php/Kingsguard\" title=\"Kingsguard\">Kingsguard</a>, Ser <a href=\"/index.php/Arryk_Cargyll\" title=\"Arryk Cargyll\">Arryk Cargyll</a>, and shifts the blame for the prince's death on him. Arryk does not understand since he was at his post with King Aegon that night. The younger knight gives in to the pressure of his <a href=\"/index.php/Lord_Commander_of_the_Kingsguard\" title=\"Lord Commander of the Kingsguard\">Lord Commander</a> and asks what he might to do repair this mistake. Criston commands him to go to <a href=\"/index.php/Dragonstone\" title=\"Dragonstone\">Dragonstone</a> and to impersonate his twin brother, Ser <a href=\"/index.php/Erryk_Cargyll\" title=\"Erryk Cargyll\">Erryk Cargyll</a>, to infiltrate the castle and kill Rhaenyra.\n</p><p>Aemond returns to the arms of Madam <a href=\"/index.php/Sylvi_(brothel_madam)\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Sylvi (brothel madam)\">Sylvi</a>, the owner of the Cock Inn. Far away from the pression of the court, the prince opens up of the older prostitute and says he regrets killing <a href=\"/index.php/Lucerys_Velaryon\" title=\"Lucerys Velaryon\">Luke</a> out of anger. She points out to him that when princes get angry it is the smallfolk who pay the price.\n</p><p><a href=\"/index.php/Hugh_Hammer\" title=\"Hugh Hammer\">Hugh</a> and his wife <a href=\"/index.php/Kat\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Kat\">Kat</a> talk about the <a href=\"/index.php/Food\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Food\">food</a> shortage in the markets of the capital due to the <a href=\"/index.php/House_Velaryon\" title=\"House Velaryon\">Velaryon</a> naval blockade. Hugh is astonished this got this bad this quickly, Kat explains that those with more means in the city have bought great quantity of food and either keep it for themselves or resell it at greater cost to profit from the situation. Still not paid for his work for the crown, Hugh is worried he might not be able to provide for his wife and his sick daughter in the near future.\n</p><p>Otto confronts Aegon after he has all the ratcatcher of the Red Keep hung. The <a href=\"/index.php/Hand_of_the_King\" title=\"Hand of the King\">Hand of the King</a> is furious as this act undoes everything the funeral procession gained them. The smallfolk are now angry at the king for killing innoncents men but Aegon is pleased as one of them was Blood's accomplice. As the discussion continues Aegon gets more irritated at his grandsire and strips him of his office. He names Ser Criston as Otto's replacement by vertue of his idea of infiltrating Dragonstone to kill Rhaenyra. Otto departs from court for <a href=\"/index.php/Oldtown\" title=\"Oldtown\">Oldtown</a>, but Alicent advices him to stop at <a href=\"/index.php/Highgarden\" title=\"Highgarden\">Highgarden</a> on his way to sway <a href=\"/index.php/House_Tyrell\" title=\"House Tyrell\">House Tyrell</a> to their cause.\n</p>\n<h3><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Driftmark\">Driftmark</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Rhaenyra_the_Cruel&amp;action=edit&amp;section=4\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: Driftmark\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h3>\n<p><a href=\"/index.php/Alyn_of_Hull\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Alyn of Hull\">Alyn of Hull</a> reunites with his brother, <a href=\"/index.php/Addam_Velaryon\" title=\"Addam Velaryon\">Addam</a>, a shipwright employed by <a href=\"/index.php/House_Velaryon\" title=\"House Velaryon\">House Velaryon</a>. Addam learned about Alyn saving Lord <a href=\"/index.php/Corlys_Velaryon\" title=\"Corlys Velaryon\">Corlys</a>'s life, he views this act as a chance for the <a href=\"/index.php/Lord_of_the_Tides\" title=\"Lord of the Tides\">Lord of the Tides</a> to favor them and change their lives for the better. Corlys and his wife, Princess <a href=\"/index.php/Rhaenys_Targaryen_(daughter_of_Aemon)\" title=\"Rhaenys Targaryen (daughter of Aemon)\">Rhaenys Targaryen</a>, discusses Daemon's depart and what he plans on doing in the <a href=\"/index.php/Riverlands\" title=\"Riverlands\">riverlands</a>. While gathering sea food on the beach, Addam spots <a href=\"/index.php/Seasmoke\" title=\"Seasmoke\">Seasmoke</a> in the sky.\n</p>\n<h3><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Dragonstone\">Dragonstone</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Rhaenyra_the_Cruel&amp;action=edit&amp;section=5\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: Dragonstone\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h3>\n<p>Rhaenyra's council discuss the news of the procession, Rhaenyra is shocked people would think her capable of such act but quickly realizes Daemon is behind it. Rhaenyra confronts him privately, he explains himself but does not take responsability. Their argument ends with Daemon storming off and leaving for <a href=\"/index.php/Harrenhal\" title=\"Harrenhal\">Harrenhal</a>. Rhaenyra is afraid of retaliations from the <a href=\"/index.php/Greens\" title=\"Greens\">Greens</a>, she commands Lady <a href=\"/index.php/Baela_Targaryen\" title=\"Baela Targaryen\">Baela Targaryen</a> to scout the King's Landing area on top her <a href=\"/index.php/Dragon\" title=\"Dragon\">dragon</a>, <a href=\"/index.php/Moondancer\" title=\"Moondancer\">Moondancer</a>, but not to engage combat.\n</p><p>Rhaenyra meets with <a href=\"/index.php/Mysaria\" title=\"Mysaria\">Mysaria</a> in the castle library, she questions her about her involvement in Jaehaerys' murder. As their duscussion progresses, Rhaenyra recognizes Mysaria as the woman used by Daemon during the stolen <a href=\"/index.php/Dragon_egg\" title=\"Dragon egg\">dragon egg</a> incident years before. Rhaenyra sees a bit of herself in Mysaria as both women where utilized by Daemon then disregarded, she decides to free her and has a passage for the <a href=\"/index.php/Free_Cities\" title=\"Free Cities\">Free Cities</a> secured for her. On her way to the ship, Mysaria spots Ser Arryk and warn the guards tough they do not believe her at once.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rhbohotds02e03.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_2-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rhbohotds02e03.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup> Arryk is successful in reaching Rhaenyra's chambers before Erryk barges into the room, the Cargyll twins starts dueling on another. Warned by Rhaenyra's <a href=\"/index.php/Handmaid\" title=\"Handmaid\">handmaid</a>, <a href=\"/index.php/Elinda_Massey\" title=\"Elinda Massey\">Elinda Massey</a>, Ser <a href=\"/index.php/Lorent_Marbrand\" title=\"Lorent Marbrand\">Lorent Marbrand</a> enters the room as well but he is anable to distinguish the two brothers apart. He protects Rhaenyra as the brothers continue their fight. Ser Erryk prevails in the end but can not live any longer knowing he has just killed his own brother, he asks forgiveness from Rhaenyra then falls on his own sword.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rhbohotds02e02.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_3-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rhbohotds02e02.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-3\">&#91;3&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Cast\">Cast</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Rhaenyra_the_Cruel&amp;action=edit&amp;section=6\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: Cast\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<h3><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Starring\">Starring</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Rhaenyra_the_Cruel&amp;action=edit&amp;section=7\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: Starring\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h3>\n<div style=\"column-count:2; column-width:300px;\"> \n<ul><li><a href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Matt_Smith\" class=\"extiw\" title=\"w:Matt Smith\">Matt Smith</a> as Prince <a href=\"/index.php/Daemon_Targaryen\" title=\"Daemon Targaryen\">Daemon Targaryen</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Emma_D%27Arcy\" class=\"extiw\" title=\"w:Emma D&#39;Arcy\">Emma D'Arcy</a> as Queen <a href=\"/index.php/Rhaenyra_Targaryen\" title=\"Rhaenyra Targaryen\">Rhaenyra Targaryen</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Olivia_Cooke\" class=\"extiw\" title=\"w:Olivia Cooke\">Olivia Cooke</a> as Queen <a href=\"/index.php/Alicent_Hightower\" title=\"Alicent Hightower\">Alicent Hightower</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Rhys_Ifans\" class=\"extiw\" title=\"w:Rhys Ifans\">Rhys Ifans</a> as Ser <a href=\"/index.php/Otto_Hightower\" title=\"Otto Hightower\">Otto Hightower</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Steve_Toussaint\" class=\"extiw\" title=\"w:Steve Toussaint\">Steve Toussaint</a> as Lord <a href=\"/index.php/Corlys_Velaryon\" title=\"Corlys Velaryon\">Corlys Velaryon</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Eve_Best\" class=\"extiw\" title=\"w:Eve Best\">Eve Best</a> as Princess <a href=\"/index.php/Rhaenys_Targaryen_(daughter_of_Aemon)\" title=\"Rhaenys Targaryen (daughter of Aemon)\">Rhaenys Targaryen</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Fabien_Frankel\" class=\"extiw\" title=\"w:Fabien Frankel\">Fabien Frankel</a> as Ser <a href=\"/index.php/Criston_Cole\" title=\"Criston Cole\">Criston Cole</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Matthew_Needham\" class=\"extiw\" title=\"w:Matthew Needham\">Matthew Needham</a> as Lord <a href=\"/index.php/Larys_Strong\" title=\"Larys Strong\">Larys Strong</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Sonoya_Mizuno\" class=\"extiw\" title=\"w:Sonoya Mizuno\">Sonoya Mizuno</a> as <a href=\"/index.php/Mysaria\" title=\"Mysaria\">Mysaria</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Tom_Glynn-Carney\" class=\"extiw\" title=\"w:Tom Glynn-Carney\">Tom Glynn-Carney</a> as King <a href=\"/index.php/Aegon_II_Targaryen\" title=\"Aegon II Targaryen\">Aegon II Targaryen</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Ewan_Mitchell\" class=\"extiw\" title=\"w:Ewan Mitchell\">Ewan Mitchell</a> as Prince <a href=\"/index.php/Aemond_Targaryen\" title=\"Aemond Targaryen\">Aemond Targaryen</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Phia_Saban\" class=\"extiw\" title=\"w:Phia Saban\">Phia Saban</a> as Queen <a href=\"/index.php/Helaena_Targaryen\" title=\"Helaena Targaryen\">Helaena Targaryen</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Harry_Collett\" class=\"extiw\" title=\"w:Harry Collett\">Harry Collett</a> as Prince <a href=\"/index.php/Jacaerys_Velaryon\" title=\"Jacaerys Velaryon\">Jacaerys Velaryon</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Bethany_Antonia\" class=\"extiw\" title=\"w:Bethany Antonia\">Bethany Antonia</a> as Lady <a href=\"/index.php/Baela_Targaryen\" title=\"Baela Targaryen\">Baela Targaryen</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Jefferson_Hall_(actor)\" class=\"extiw\" title=\"w:Jefferson Hal